SDN_question = "\nQuestion: Which of the following are examples of control plane operations? Select all that apply.\na. Rate-limiting traffic so that the overall sending rate does not exceed a certain throughput.\nb. Determining that a user's MAC address is authentic before allowing it to send traffic on the network.\nc. Load balancing traffic across two output ports based on the hash of each packet's source IP address.\nd. Determining the forwarding path that satisfies an access control policy.\ne. Computing a shortest path routing tree.\nResponse: {\"answer\": \"b, d, e\", \"explanation\": \"a. This operation can be performed in the data plane.\nb. Controllers such as Ethane and Resonance perform this type of function.\nc. This operation can be performed entirely in the data plane.\nd. This is a path computation, which is a control-plane function.\ne. This is a path computation, which is a control-plane function.\nTherefore, the correct answers are options b, d, and e, which are all control plane operations.\", \"confidence\": 1, \"sources\": [\"https://www.splunk.com/en_us/blog/learn/control-plane-vs-data-plane.html#:~:text=The%20control%20plane%20is%20responsible,concept%20of%20managing%20network%20configuration\",   \"https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3371934.3371963\"]}"

